{"id":14880979,"mediaExerciseId":"3bc496b1-3e64-48cb-a853-cc0feef39a96","exerciseName":"41","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":187,"solutions":[{"id":6024636,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine the highest rate we can afford on a 60 month APR loan monthly compounding if we want to borrow an amount of $115,000 and the maximum monthly payment we can make is $2,250.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/33451d8ed137f51577358bdd90947207/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/33451d8ed137f51577358bdd90947207/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's discuss what an APR is.\n\nAPR, the *Annual Percentage Rate* also referred to as the stated rate, is calculated by multiplying the nominal rate by the number of periods in a year, representing the annual rate a lender can quote its customer as prescribed by laws.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/db0f37044378d7c4db75d53797ac2d36/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/db0f37044378d7c4db75d53797ac2d36/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, to determine the annual percentage rate, calculate the monthly rate of the loan.\n\nTo find the rate, we will utilize the spreadsheet function RATE. The rate function is a financial function that calculates the rate based on the period, present value, and future value. The rate spreadsheet formula is as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nRATE&=(nper,pmt,pv,[fv],[type]) \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\nWhere:\n\n$nper$, which refers to the period\\\n$pmt$, which means the constant payment\\\n$pv$, which represent the present value\\\n$fv$, the future value\\\n$type$, which indicates the basis of the calculation, either year-end or beginning of the year\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":422,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/d7aba36b5c4605860970fb3f33be887f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":213,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/d7aba36b5c4605860970fb3f33be887f/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"We will consider the following details in finding the rate:\n\n| Particulars   |           |\n|---------------|-----------|\n| Present value | $115,000 |\n| Monthly payment        | $2,250    |\n| Period        | 60    |","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/075ac7a29fc184d00de2c97352b16e26/lateximg_large.png","width":1306},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/075ac7a29fc184d00de2c97352b16e26/lateximg.png","width":653}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now calculate the monthly rate using the rate function on the spreadsheet.\n\n!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/69dcb4d5-1421-49cd-86a9-dcea5b015f70-1642249232146737.png)\n\nHence, as can be seen in our calculation, the monthly rate is 0.542%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Finally, considering the rate from the previous step, calculate the annual percentage rate. The APR can be calculate using the following formula:\n\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{APR} &=12\\times\\text{Interest rate}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/41ed037e1dd61031af0f3e3eeec2fc91/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/41ed037e1dd61031af0f3e3eeec2fc91/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now calculate the annual percentage rate of the loan:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{APR} &= 12\\times0.542\\%\n\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\bf6.50\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**Based on our calculation, the higher rate we can afford on the 60-month loan is 6.50%**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":250,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/3ca162017e05d1190566d3d5ba99b10b/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":126,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/530a6c2f2682bd6d18610c936beb9b8d/3ca162017e05d1190566d3d5ba99b10b/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"To conclude, we determined the highest rate we can afford on the 60-month loan, which is 6.50%, by calculating the annual percentage rate. The monthly rate is computed by considering the monthly payment, period, and present value.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"cfdae565-32f2-4a76-88dd-bedd4441b8f2","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":8}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880980,"exerciseName":"42","page":187,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2134031a-381a-4e59-974f-b37f0c357e3e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-42-2134031a-381a-4e59-974f-b37f0c357e3e"},{"id":14880981,"exerciseName":"43","page":187,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"181e5ffc-46c7-4ad7-893e-f0bb2a268e64","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-43-181e5ffc-46c7-4ad7-893e-f0bb2a268e64"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880978,"exerciseName":"40","page":187,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6c51368e-d090-4062-b2dd-1145b5920951","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-40-6c51368e-d090-4062-b2dd-1145b5920951"},{"id":14880977,"exerciseName":"39","page":187,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"90a43641-5a11-4268-b15f-22b9d224032c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-97812